WEBVTT

00:47.709 --> 00:49.333
(FAINT KNOCKING)

00:54.166 --> 00:56.000
(KNOCKING CONTINUES)

01:10.500 --> 01:12.291
(SOFTLY) Honey.

01:12.291 --> 01:13.834
Honey, wake up.

01:13.834 --> 01:15.792
-What is it?
-Wake up.

01:15.792 --> 01:18.083
It sounds like somebody's
knocking.

01:18.083 --> 01:20.625
(KNOCKING CONTINUES)

01:20.625 --> 01:23.458
All right. Hit the lights.

01:23.458 --> 01:24.875
(GRUNTING)

01:29.834 --> 01:31.709
(KNOCKING CONTINUES)

01:35.667 --> 01:36.834
What are you doing?

01:36.834 --> 01:38.333
Stay right here, Mary.

01:57.083 --> 01:59.500
-(SIGHS)
-(KNOCKING CONTINUES)

02:12.542 --> 02:13.709
(THUD)

02:25.291 --> 02:26.709
(DOG BARKING)

02:46.208 --> 02:47.458
(SIGHS)

03:11.583 --> 03:13.083
What was it?

03:13.750 --> 03:15.291
It was nothing.

03:17.417 --> 03:18.583
Come on.

03:19.417 --> 03:20.792
Come here.

03:21.625 --> 03:23.250
God.

03:23.250 --> 03:25.166
(RELIEVED SIGH)

03:25.166 --> 03:27.208
-(RELIEVED SIGH)
-(RATTLING)

03:27.208 --> 03:28.583
What is that?

03:28.583 --> 03:30.125
(CLATTERING)

03:32.250 --> 03:33.333
(PANTING)

03:33.333 --> 03:34.834
I'm calling the police.

03:38.125 --> 03:41.125
Hi, I'm at
3301 Cameron Street.

03:41.125 --> 03:43.458
I think somebody is trying
to break into our house.

03:43.458 --> 03:44.667
(DOOR CREAKS SHUT)

03:44.667 --> 03:46.417
Who's down there?

03:49.917 --> 03:51.250
MAN: Little pig.

03:59.583 --> 04:00.625
MARY: Oh, God!

04:03.625 --> 04:04.959
(PANTING)

04:18.041 --> 04:19.375
(PANTING)

04:23.125 --> 04:24.625
MAN: They're in here.

04:38.125 --> 04:39.458
-(THUDDING)
-(GRUNTS)

04:40.583 --> 04:42.125
(DOG BARKING)

04:48.375 --> 04:50.500
John, there's someone
out there!

04:55.375 --> 04:56.834
(DOORKNOB RATTLING)

05:13.959 --> 05:16.250
(SIREN WAILING IN DISTANCE)

05:20.291 --> 05:21.750
(CAR DOOR OPENS)

05:31.333 --> 05:32.875
(DOG BARKING)

05:38.208 --> 05:40.041
LAPD! I'm coming in!

05:54.542 --> 05:56.542
(LIGHT SWITCH CLICKING)

06:52.625 --> 06:54.166
(BREATHES SHARPLY)

07:17.458 --> 07:19.333
(BREATHING SHAKILY)

07:30.125 --> 07:31.834
(DOOR CREAKING)

07:42.083 --> 07:43.500
(RATTLING)

07:53.458 --> 07:54.709
-(DOOR CREAKS)
-(GASPS)

07:54.709 --> 07:57.041
-Don't shoot! Don't shoot!
-Don't shoot! Don't shoot!

07:57.041 --> 07:58.709
(PANTING)

07:58.709 --> 08:00.875
POLICE OFFICER:
Detective Clarkin.

08:02.125 --> 08:03.542
The missus says
she got a visual,

08:03.542 --> 08:05.458
but she's fuzzy on details.

08:05.458 --> 08:08.125
It was dark.
She was upstairs looking down
through her window.

08:08.125 --> 08:12.000
Said she was pretty sure
she saw a white female,
but couldn't guarantee.

08:12.000 --> 08:13.875
She's still a little shaken,
but, uh,

08:13.875 --> 08:15.917
maybe when she calms
down a little...

08:18.166 --> 08:20.875
CLARKIN: Every day
it's something new here.

08:22.333 --> 08:25.583
-At least the weather's nice.
-(CHUCKLES)

08:25.583 --> 08:28.458
-Those the home owners?
-Yeah. Right this way.

08:28.458 --> 08:30.959
(INDISTINCT
POLICE RADIO CHATTER)

08:40.000 --> 08:42.917
Think of any reason
someone might
wanna do this to you?

08:42.917 --> 08:44.125
MARY: No.

08:44.125 --> 08:46.750
Disgruntled employee,
upset family member, neighbor?

08:46.750 --> 08:50.250
No! No! No one we know
would do something like this.

08:50.250 --> 08:51.291
Of course.

08:51.875 --> 08:53.792
Had to ask.

08:53.792 --> 08:55.542
There's been a rash
of home invasions

08:55.542 --> 08:57.333
over the past few weeks,

08:57.333 --> 08:59.750
so I'm sure this was
in connection with those.

08:59.750 --> 09:01.583
But who would
do something like this?

09:01.583 --> 09:04.709
Runaways, hippies,
radicals, dropouts.

09:04.709 --> 09:07.709
You name it, you got
it all here in California.

09:07.709 --> 09:10.291
Look, I've got a few theories,

09:10.291 --> 09:12.417
but nothing
I can share at the moment.

09:12.417 --> 09:16.000
The good news is,
they've all been
relatively minor infractions.

09:16.000 --> 09:18.667
People sneaking in,
moving things around.

09:18.667 --> 09:19.959
MARY: Excuse me, Officer.

09:19.959 --> 09:23.250
This doesn't seem
to be something minor.

09:23.250 --> 09:25.000
It certainly didn't
feel minor.

09:25.000 --> 09:28.083
No. No, I'm sure it didn't.

09:30.208 --> 09:35.208
I admit, this one seems like
they're stepping things up.

09:35.208 --> 09:37.875
Who knows what might
have happened if you
didn't call when you did.

09:37.875 --> 09:39.709
I just don't understand.

09:39.709 --> 09:43.125
They're crazy, dear.
Crazy people do crazy things.

09:44.333 --> 09:46.375
(MARIACHI MUSIC PLAYING)

10:04.834 --> 10:07.000
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

10:08.125 --> 10:10.208
WAITRESS:
Fuller. Party of three.

10:12.625 --> 10:14.625
Hola.  This way, please.

10:15.959 --> 10:17.834
(SINGING IN SPANISH)

10:38.417 --> 10:40.417
(CHEERING AND APPLAUSE)

10:40.417 --> 10:41.709
Make a wish.

10:43.291 --> 10:45.417
(CHEERING AND APPLAUDING)

10:49.834 --> 10:51.375
Happy birthday, Abby.

10:51.375 --> 10:53.625
My birthday is in October.

10:53.625 --> 10:55.208
-Ah.
-Oh.

10:55.208 --> 10:56.500
We know.

10:56.500 --> 10:57.875
But aren't birthday parties

10:57.875 --> 11:00.709
so much more fun
than going away parties?

11:01.959 --> 11:03.291
What? Not my idea.

11:03.291 --> 11:05.417
-What was your idea?
-WOJCIECH: I don't know.

11:05.417 --> 11:07.917
Kidnap you. Keep you here
forever and ever.

11:07.917 --> 11:09.917
-How sweet.
-Thanks.

11:09.917 --> 11:11.875
SHARON:
Wait, wait, wait, wait.

11:11.875 --> 11:13.458
One more thing.

11:15.333 --> 11:18.417
What's a birthday party
without presents?

11:18.417 --> 11:19.625
Sharon.

11:26.667 --> 11:28.083
Beautiful.

11:34.709 --> 11:36.625
(CLICKS TONGUE) Aw.

11:36.625 --> 11:38.750
-I took it when we were...
-I know.

11:39.291 --> 11:40.709
It's Zuma.

11:41.375 --> 11:42.750
Our beach.

11:43.417 --> 11:46.083
It's beautiful, Sharon.

11:46.083 --> 11:48.709
We always said it had
a mystical hold over us.

11:48.709 --> 11:50.208
Yeah.

11:50.208 --> 11:52.834
WOJCIECH: This is actually
where we first met.
You remember that?

11:52.834 --> 11:54.625
-Yeah.
-That bonfire party?

11:54.625 --> 11:56.125
That was a good party.

11:57.333 --> 11:58.917
JAY: Credit where
credit's due.

11:58.917 --> 12:00.667
In this case, to me.

12:04.583 --> 12:05.917
I'm gonna miss that beach.

12:05.917 --> 12:07.917
-And we're gonna miss you.
-Yeah.

12:07.917 --> 12:10.125
So, when you get sick
of Boston

12:10.125 --> 12:11.959
and decide to come back,

12:13.458 --> 12:15.625
it'll be the first place
that we go.

12:16.792 --> 12:19.166
Thank you. I love it.

12:21.458 --> 12:23.583
(SHE'S NOT THERE  PLAYING)

13:11.041 --> 13:13.500
ABIGAIL:
Sharon, who's here now?

13:25.125 --> 13:27.041
(CAR RADIO TURNS OFF)

13:29.792 --> 13:31.041
Thank you.

13:31.041 --> 13:32.667
(GIGGLES)

13:32.667 --> 13:34.041
Thank you.

13:35.709 --> 13:38.834
You promised you weren't
gonna throw a party.

13:38.834 --> 13:41.166
And I kept my promise.

13:41.166 --> 13:43.041
But you know how it is.

13:43.041 --> 13:45.000
People show up
whenever they feel like it.

13:45.000 --> 13:48.375
Well, maybe you should
rethink that policy
when the baby arrives.

13:48.375 --> 13:49.709
(SHARON GIGGLES)

14:04.375 --> 14:07.083
RADIO JOCKEY:
That song haunts me.
It just does.

14:07.083 --> 14:08.667
Mmm-mmm-mmm.

14:08.667 --> 14:10.959
Nothing else to say but that.

14:10.959 --> 14:12.959
Sixteen minutes before 11:00.

14:12.959 --> 14:15.709
This is the HJB program,

14:15.709 --> 14:18.291
where we have
a good time all the time.

14:18.291 --> 14:20.750
We're gonna bop
around all night

14:20.750 --> 14:23.083
having fun,
doing things, you know.

14:23.083 --> 14:26.959
Stick around for your favorite
blues and R&B tunes.

14:26.959 --> 14:31.709
72 degrees in Los Angeles
right now,
76 in the Valley.

14:32.917 --> 14:35.125
(CAR RADIO PLAYING FAINTLY)

14:52.291 --> 14:54.166
(CAR RADIO TURNS OFF)

15:16.875 --> 15:18.834
ABIGAIL: Okay, just tell me
what's going on.

15:18.834 --> 15:20.959
SHARON: I have no idea
what's going on.

15:21.583 --> 15:24.417
But let's find out.

15:24.417 --> 15:27.667
(SOFTLY) Sharon!
You can't just look in there.

15:27.667 --> 15:29.542
What? Yes.

15:29.542 --> 15:32.458
I'm just investigating.
It's fine.

15:33.125 --> 15:34.375
(TWIG SNAPS)

15:36.709 --> 15:38.291
(ZIPPING PANTS)

15:38.291 --> 15:40.291
-Sorry.
-(BOTH CHUCKLING)

15:42.333 --> 15:43.750
Is William around?

15:43.750 --> 15:46.792
He rents the guest house.
It's just right around there.

15:46.792 --> 15:48.000
Thanks.

15:49.000 --> 15:50.834
You know, you look familiar.

15:50.834 --> 15:52.041
You don't.

15:52.041 --> 15:53.834
You sure we've never
met each other?

15:53.834 --> 15:57.667
If we did, you'd remember.
I can promise you that.

15:57.667 --> 16:00.208
I'll definitely remember
for the next time, then.

16:00.208 --> 16:01.834
You two take care, now.

16:04.375 --> 16:05.709
(GRUNTS)

16:09.375 --> 16:12.250
Needs a few years to mature,
but overall, not bad.

16:12.250 --> 16:14.542
-Oh, my God. You're terrible.
-(GIGGLES)

16:14.542 --> 16:15.917
What's gonna happen
after I'm gone?

16:15.917 --> 16:18.125
Who's gonna keep you
in line then?

16:18.125 --> 16:20.542
Aw. You don't have to go, Abs.

16:20.542 --> 16:22.709
You could stay here.
There's plenty of room.

16:22.709 --> 16:24.041
And then what?

16:24.041 --> 16:27.333
And then...
Ah, who knows?

16:27.333 --> 16:29.875
Isn't that the exciting
part about life?

16:29.875 --> 16:31.208
(FIRE WORKS EXPLODING)

16:34.583 --> 16:36.375
See, you say
something like that,

16:36.375 --> 16:37.875
and fireworks go off.

16:37.875 --> 16:40.208
I say something like that
and I'd get a flat tire.

16:40.208 --> 16:43.291
-Oh, don't be silly.
-(GIGGLES) It's true.

16:47.250 --> 16:49.417
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATION)

16:52.333 --> 16:54.041
(ABIGAIL AND SHARON GIGGLE)

16:54.709 --> 16:56.750
SHARON: Guys!

16:56.750 --> 16:58.792
Turn on the lights
when you come in, will you?

17:06.458 --> 17:07.541
Jay?

17:08.250 --> 17:09.583
Wojciech?

17:10.916 --> 17:12.250
You guys?

17:18.165 --> 17:19.959
(FEEDBACK)

17:19.959 --> 17:22.791
STEVEN: You won't believe
the clarity, man.

17:22.791 --> 17:24.000
Dig that platter.

17:25.458 --> 17:26.791
That tonearm?

17:26.791 --> 17:28.583
That's new, too.

17:28.583 --> 17:31.792
The old model
had that clunky plastic one.
Remember that?

17:31.792 --> 17:32.875
(SIGHS)

17:32.875 --> 17:35.166
It's really far out, Steve.

17:35.166 --> 17:36.625
Four speeds.

17:37.291 --> 17:38.625
Volume.

17:38.625 --> 17:40.166
Tone controls.

17:42.041 --> 17:44.792
What more could you need?
Am I right?

17:46.583 --> 17:48.250
How does it sound?

17:48.250 --> 17:50.291
Oh, out of sight, man.

17:51.542 --> 17:53.667
But are you sure
you wanna hear her?

17:54.208 --> 17:55.333
Yeah.

17:57.000 --> 17:58.917
Why wouldn't I?

17:58.917 --> 18:01.917
Because as soon as you
hear this beauty

18:01.917 --> 18:04.250
no way are you letting me
leave here with her.

18:04.250 --> 18:05.667
(CHUCKLES)

18:08.834 --> 18:11.333
I've got the scratch,
if that's what you're asking.

18:11.333 --> 18:12.458
(CHUCKLES)

18:12.458 --> 18:14.625
(INHALES AND EXHALES)

18:15.625 --> 18:18.750
Here, put these on.

18:18.750 --> 18:22.000
After this,
you won't need acid
to see the music, man.

18:22.000 --> 18:23.375
(LAUGHING)

18:24.667 --> 18:26.000
Okay.

18:29.208 --> 18:30.709
Won't hurt though, right?

18:30.709 --> 18:32.500
(CHUCKLES) Not a bit, man.

18:40.333 --> 18:41.709
(EXHALES)

18:55.625 --> 18:57.917
(CRIMSON AND CLOVER  PLAYING)

20:05.083 --> 20:06.417
(SONG STOPS)

20:06.417 --> 20:07.625
(GASPS)

20:07.625 --> 20:10.625
-What'd you do that for?
-(CHUCKLES)

20:10.625 --> 20:13.917
He who pays the piper
calls the tune.

20:15.125 --> 20:16.875
What does that mean?

20:16.875 --> 20:19.625
Means, you gonna pony up
the dough for it, or what?

20:32.041 --> 20:34.125
Hi, Mom. You're up late.

20:35.208 --> 20:36.458
I know.

20:37.625 --> 20:39.125
Yes, I know.

20:41.208 --> 20:43.291
I'm excited to see you, too.

20:43.792 --> 20:45.166
(CHUCKLES) Yeah.

20:49.041 --> 20:50.625
Huh?

20:50.625 --> 20:54.291
Oh, I did.
The dress was delivered today.

20:54.291 --> 20:57.166
Yeah, right, just in time.
It's...

20:58.375 --> 20:59.583
(SHARON GIGGLES)

20:59.583 --> 21:00.959
It's beautiful.

21:01.667 --> 21:03.667
I'll wear it tomorrow.

21:04.667 --> 21:06.000
Thank you.

21:06.000 --> 21:08.333
Okay, get some sleep.

21:08.333 --> 21:10.041
I love you, too.

21:14.333 --> 21:17.166
-I guess fashion
really is dead.
-We should bury it.

21:17.166 --> 21:19.083
Let's go get some shovels.

21:19.083 --> 21:21.000
(ABIGAIL AND SHARON GIGGLE)

21:21.000 --> 21:23.542
ABIGAIL: She's making me
wear it tomorrow.

21:32.500 --> 21:35.500
Hey, who's that chick
that lives up
at the main house?

21:35.500 --> 21:36.792
She looked familiar.

21:36.792 --> 21:40.208
Uh, she's been in
a bunch of movies
and TV shows.

21:40.208 --> 21:41.458
(CRACKERS BURSTING)

21:41.458 --> 21:44.208
You, like,
party with her ever?

21:46.458 --> 21:48.667
Sometimes, yeah.

21:48.667 --> 21:52.333
She and her old man
got a real vibe
going on up there, so...

21:52.333 --> 21:54.166
People come and go.

21:57.208 --> 21:58.583
We good?

21:58.583 --> 21:59.709
(CHUCKLES)

21:59.709 --> 22:01.375
(CLICKS TONGUE)

22:01.375 --> 22:03.083
All right. Peace, man.

22:11.542 --> 22:13.208
(CHUCKLES)

22:13.208 --> 22:15.250
(FIREWORKS EXPLODING)

22:27.375 --> 22:29.458
Fourth of July
was over a month ago.

22:29.458 --> 22:31.000
What are people thinking?

22:31.000 --> 22:34.375
I don't know.
End of summer, maybe?

22:34.375 --> 22:37.083
People use any excuse
to blow stuff up.

22:42.250 --> 22:43.375
So,

22:44.208 --> 22:46.250
you wanted to talk?

22:46.250 --> 22:47.375
Mmm.

22:47.792 --> 22:49.208
Mmm, yeah.

22:49.959 --> 22:51.250
(SIGHS) No.

22:51.250 --> 22:53.208
(STAMMERS)
I don't know anymore.

22:53.208 --> 22:55.083
You don't know what?

22:56.250 --> 22:57.917
I feel...

22:57.917 --> 23:02.000
I feel like maybe I had you
figured out all wrong somehow.

23:02.625 --> 23:04.041
How so?

23:04.041 --> 23:06.208
Because I never
figured you to be
the sort of trust fund girl

23:06.208 --> 23:08.125
who would go crawling back
to mommy and daddy

23:08.125 --> 23:09.834
as soon as they threatened
to stop sending the dough.

23:09.834 --> 23:11.458
I'm not crawling back to them.

23:11.458 --> 23:13.291
Oh, no. They're flying
you first class.

23:15.917 --> 23:17.750
That's bad. I'm sorry.

23:20.917 --> 23:24.750
I'm not leaving
because my parents
threatened to cut me off.

23:28.291 --> 23:31.834
I'm leaving because I feel
like it's time to move on.

23:32.792 --> 23:34.792
I don't fit in here.

23:34.792 --> 23:38.625
This whole city is populated
by people who feel
like they don't fit in.

23:39.750 --> 23:41.959
Look, I never told you this,

23:41.959 --> 23:43.875
but a year ago,

23:43.875 --> 23:45.959
I was gonna give up.

23:45.959 --> 23:49.250
Just pack it all in.

23:49.250 --> 23:53.625
But then I convinced
myself to give it
another couple of weeks.

23:53.625 --> 23:55.166
What happened?

23:57.333 --> 23:58.667
I met you

23:59.917 --> 24:02.000
on that beach.

24:02.000 --> 24:03.166
And it was then I decided

24:03.166 --> 24:05.208
that I was gonna give myself
as long as it takes.

24:05.208 --> 24:08.333
Because no matter what
happens with the business
and all that,

24:08.333 --> 24:09.959
there was always Abigail.

24:09.959 --> 24:11.917
No, Wojciech, you...

24:11.917 --> 24:13.125
(CHUCKLES)

24:13.125 --> 24:15.667
You can't make me responsible
for your dreams, too.

24:15.667 --> 24:18.291
I'm not. I'm not.
I'm just trying
to convince you to stay,

24:18.291 --> 24:19.667
so you don't give up on yours.

24:22.709 --> 24:24.583
There's a reason
that you don't fit in.

24:24.583 --> 24:27.500
It's not because
you're different.

24:27.500 --> 24:30.542
It's absolutely
because you're special.

24:33.542 --> 24:35.417
(FIREWORKS EXPLODING)

24:36.625 --> 24:39.250
I wish it could work out,
Wojciech.

24:50.375 --> 24:52.458
SHARON:
It's not even late, Amy.

24:52.458 --> 24:55.709
Plus, I know Abby
would love to see you
before she leaves.

24:55.709 --> 24:58.041
I could use you as well.

24:59.083 --> 25:01.750
I don't wanna be alone
when she goes.

25:02.917 --> 25:05.000
Especially right away.

25:05.000 --> 25:06.917
(CHUCKLES)

25:06.917 --> 25:09.625
No. Because they're boys.

25:09.625 --> 25:12.750
And plus, Jay pretends
like I'm not even...

25:12.750 --> 25:14.417
(LINE BREAKING)

25:14.417 --> 25:15.583
Hello?

25:17.417 --> 25:18.959
Hello?

25:18.959 --> 25:20.542
Hello, hello.

25:28.083 --> 25:30.625
(MARY HAD A LITTLE LAMB
PLAYING)

25:43.583 --> 25:45.500
(CAR RADIO FAINTLY PLAYING)

25:55.625 --> 25:56.959
Shit.

26:47.500 --> 26:49.333
(FIREWORK EXPLODES)

27:19.041 --> 27:20.709
-(HONKING)
-Come on, man.

27:21.291 --> 27:22.750
Out of the way!

27:24.166 --> 27:26.083
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING)

27:45.709 --> 27:46.875
(THUD)

27:46.875 --> 27:48.250
(GIGGLING)

27:53.458 --> 27:54.667
(GUN CLICKS)

27:54.667 --> 27:56.291
No, no, please. I have money.

28:02.083 --> 28:03.125
(GRUNTS)

28:07.250 --> 28:08.917
(MUFFLED PROTESTS)

28:35.250 --> 28:36.959
-(DOOR OPENS)
-(GASPS)

28:36.959 --> 28:38.417
(CHUCKLES)

28:38.417 --> 28:40.250
-Jay.
-Sorry. Sorry.

28:40.250 --> 28:41.667
Are those the fireworks--

28:41.667 --> 28:44.291
Oh, the fireworks
that you threw away?

28:44.291 --> 28:45.750
You got them out of the trash?

28:45.750 --> 28:48.583
You threw away
my fireworks, Sharon.

28:48.583 --> 28:51.583
-Sharon, Sharon.
-Well, you nearly
blew your hand off.

28:51.583 --> 28:53.000
It's just my finger!

28:53.000 --> 28:55.500
You're overreacting.
It wasn't my hand.

28:55.500 --> 28:58.417
-No, no, no! Not my couch.
Not my couch.
-(SIGHS)

29:06.917 --> 29:08.583
(SPRINKLER CLICKING)

29:23.750 --> 29:26.166
(SPRINKLER CONTINUES CLICKING)

29:58.875 --> 29:59.875
(JAY WHISTLES)

29:59.875 --> 30:02.458
Doesn't look like
that's a celebratory shot.

30:02.458 --> 30:04.417
(STAMMERS) Just don't.

30:05.834 --> 30:07.375
Phew. All right, listen.

30:07.375 --> 30:10.375
I got something for you
that's gonna make you
feel groovy, okay?

30:10.375 --> 30:13.208
And since we're
all about "Sharon"
around here...

30:16.834 --> 30:19.375
You take two of these,
and it'll cure your heartache.

30:19.375 --> 30:21.208
No. Thanks, but no.

30:21.208 --> 30:22.792
Oh?

30:22.792 --> 30:25.709
All right. Well, if not this,
there's one more thing
I want you to try.

30:25.709 --> 30:27.166
Now,

30:27.166 --> 30:30.208
-her name's Gloria,
and she is all about sharing.
-(CHUCKLES)

30:30.208 --> 30:31.375
Jay.

30:33.375 --> 30:34.417
Hey.

30:35.875 --> 30:37.083
Don't listen to him.

30:38.083 --> 30:40.250
I'm sorry girls are crazy.

30:40.250 --> 30:44.125
But I know her,
and she'll come around.

30:44.125 --> 30:47.458
It's gonna be a little tough
for her to come around
given that she's in Boston.

30:47.458 --> 30:50.417
-(CHUCKLES) Ignore him.
-It's a long ways away.

30:50.417 --> 30:51.917
Where are you going?

30:51.917 --> 30:53.917
I could use a walk.

30:53.917 --> 30:55.917
I need some time to think.

31:56.083 --> 31:57.625
Oh, thank God.

32:00.333 --> 32:02.333
(FAINT KNOCKING)

32:20.041 --> 32:21.667
(DOOR OPENING)

32:23.041 --> 32:24.333
(DOOR CLOSING)

32:35.625 --> 32:37.375
(BLENDER WHIRRING)

32:47.625 --> 32:49.041
-Hey! You're just in time.
-ABIGAIL: Hey.

32:49.041 --> 32:50.834
-Did you guys hear the...
-I can't, what's that?

32:50.834 --> 32:52.291
Did you hear that?

32:52.291 --> 32:54.333
-You gotta speak up
because the blender's...
-(TURNS OFF BLENDER)

32:54.333 --> 32:55.667
Why would you do that?

32:55.667 --> 32:56.625
There was...

32:56.625 --> 32:57.917
Listen, if you're looking
for Wojciech,

32:57.917 --> 32:59.917
he went on one
of his long walks.

32:59.917 --> 33:01.709
Did you guys hear
that knocking?

33:01.709 --> 33:03.750
-What knocking?
-(WHISTLING)

33:03.750 --> 33:05.875
-Oh, God! Jay!
-Oh, oh, oh, sorry!

33:05.875 --> 33:07.250
(LAUGHING)

33:07.250 --> 33:08.375
(SHARON GRUNTS)

33:08.375 --> 33:10.667
I'm sorry. I thought
the lid was still on.

33:10.667 --> 33:12.375
Oh! You're already blitzed.

33:12.375 --> 33:14.041
(FAINT KNOCKING)

33:14.041 --> 33:17.208
That's probably Amy.
I told her to come over.

33:17.208 --> 33:20.291
Will you let her in
while I change?

33:20.291 --> 33:23.000
If it was Amy,
wouldn't she just come
to the front door?

33:23.000 --> 33:25.750
Abs, please,
will you let her in?

33:25.750 --> 33:27.583
(KNOCKING CONTINUES)

33:43.625 --> 33:44.750
Amy?

34:11.458 --> 34:13.333
(SWING CREAKING)

34:17.166 --> 34:18.250
Amy?

34:27.125 --> 34:28.625
ABIGAIL: Amy?

34:49.542 --> 34:51.875
(LIL' RED RIDING HOOD  PLAYING)

35:43.709 --> 35:45.250
(MUSIC STOPS)

35:50.709 --> 35:53.083
MAN 1 ON TV: Mexico City.
We left on Monday.

35:53.083 --> 35:55.250
-MAN 2 ON TV:
Where do you want to go?
-MAN 1: San Lorenzo.

35:55.250 --> 35:56.834
MAN 1: How far is it?
Do you know?

35:56.834 --> 35:58.500
MAN 2: Who knows how
the bridges are?

35:58.500 --> 35:59.875
Maybe a couple of hours.

35:59.875 --> 36:02.208
MAN 3 ON TV: A police car went
by just before sundown.

36:02.208 --> 36:03.709
Ah!

36:03.709 --> 36:05.166
MAN 3: They didn't come back.
So, maybe they got
through okay.

36:05.166 --> 36:06.375
JAY: "The Big Boom."

36:06.375 --> 36:07.500
(JAY CHUCKLES)

36:07.500 --> 36:08.709
MAN 3: Who knows?

36:08.709 --> 36:12.250
The telephone lines are down
since the earthquake.

36:12.250 --> 36:14.583
MAN 2: Thanks a lot.
See you later...

36:14.583 --> 36:15.792
(JAY CHUCKLES)

36:16.792 --> 36:18.250
"The Bully."

36:18.917 --> 36:20.792
(IMITATES EXPLOSION)

36:37.000 --> 36:38.083
Holy shit.

36:57.208 --> 36:59.291
Hey, man. You all right?

37:02.291 --> 37:03.333
What the--

37:07.250 --> 37:09.333
What the fuck! Who are you?

37:18.166 --> 37:19.667
(GRUNTING) Come on!

37:23.625 --> 37:24.792
Shit!

37:27.291 --> 37:28.542
(WOJCIECH GRUNTS)

37:28.542 --> 37:29.625
(THUDDING)

37:34.917 --> 37:36.333
(RATTLING)

38:10.709 --> 38:13.000
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING)

38:26.125 --> 38:27.542
(RATTLING)

38:30.542 --> 38:31.583
Hey.

39:16.250 --> 39:17.625
(BEADS RATTLING)

39:49.750 --> 39:51.625
(RATTLING CONTINUES)

40:22.542 --> 40:24.041
(BOTH GASP)

40:24.041 --> 40:25.500
Oh, my God!

40:26.250 --> 40:27.583
Shit.

40:27.583 --> 40:28.917
I'm sorry.

40:28.917 --> 40:30.375
-(SIGHS) Sorry...
-Abby.

40:30.375 --> 40:31.834
I'm sorry.

40:31.834 --> 40:33.166
What are you doing?

40:33.166 --> 40:36.000
I saw someone in the hallway.
I swear she walked in here.

40:36.000 --> 40:37.750
-What? Who?
-I...

40:37.750 --> 40:39.000
I don't know. She waved to me.

40:39.000 --> 40:41.709
So, I thought,
maybe she was
one of your friends.

40:43.000 --> 40:44.125
(THUDDING)

41:14.542 --> 41:16.333
Is that her?

41:16.333 --> 41:18.709
I can't tell. Maybe.

41:28.583 --> 41:30.166
Freaky.

41:30.166 --> 41:32.542
She must be
on some kind of a crazy trip.

41:32.542 --> 41:33.625
JAY: Who?

41:33.625 --> 41:35.291
Just this girl we saw.

41:35.291 --> 41:37.375
-Is she cute?
-(FRUSTRATED SIGH)

41:37.375 --> 41:39.083
Where's Wojciech?

41:48.250 --> 41:49.625
ABIGAIL: Wojciech?

41:58.750 --> 42:00.750
SHARON: Abby?

42:00.750 --> 42:03.250
Abby, come back inside.

42:03.250 --> 42:05.709
He's probably way down
the canyon by now.

42:05.709 --> 42:07.041
He'll be back.

42:08.583 --> 42:09.709
Abby.

42:10.583 --> 42:12.250
No, don't.

42:12.250 --> 42:13.750
Stay inside.

42:16.375 --> 42:17.792
(TV PLAYING)

42:53.625 --> 42:55.291
Can we calm down, please?

43:01.417 --> 43:03.500
You're really
starting to freak me out.

43:03.500 --> 43:05.625
Good, because
I'm already freaked out.

43:05.625 --> 43:07.375
I don't feel safe.

43:07.375 --> 43:09.917
We've gone through
the house twice already.

43:09.917 --> 43:13.500
I just wanna be sure
if they're outside,
they stay outside.

43:21.917 --> 43:24.291
(THE STAR-SPANGLED BANNER
PLAYING ON TV)

43:54.875 --> 43:56.500
(JAY GRUNTING)

44:00.208 --> 44:01.417
(JAY YELLS)

44:02.542 --> 44:03.917
What was that?

44:18.041 --> 44:19.375
(PANTING)

44:21.875 --> 44:23.333
(BEADS RATTLING)

44:28.542 --> 44:29.875
(DOOR OPENS)

44:29.875 --> 44:30.917
Jay?

44:36.291 --> 44:38.041
SHARON: Jay?

44:38.041 --> 44:39.583
ABIGAIL: Wait.

44:41.583 --> 44:42.709
Jay?

44:45.333 --> 44:46.375
Jay!

44:53.250 --> 44:54.417
Sharon.

44:54.417 --> 44:55.750
Wojciech?

44:56.583 --> 44:58.625
(FIREWORKS EXPLODING)

45:00.583 --> 45:01.625
Jay!

45:02.417 --> 45:03.667
(SOFTLY) What are they...

45:03.667 --> 45:06.208
No, I told you, stay inside.

45:09.834 --> 45:11.458
(GLASS SHATTERING)

45:14.500 --> 45:16.417
(CRACKLING)

45:16.417 --> 45:18.166
(BLENDER WHIRRING)

45:35.792 --> 45:36.834
Be careful.

45:41.417 --> 45:42.792
(WHIRRING STOPS)

45:43.792 --> 45:45.458
(METAL CREAKING)

45:56.709 --> 45:58.041
(STATIC NOISE FROM TV)

46:00.625 --> 46:01.834
What's happening?

46:02.709 --> 46:04.041
I don't know.

46:50.041 --> 46:51.041
Jay?

46:52.083 --> 46:53.667
(STATIC NOISE CONTINUES)

46:59.792 --> 47:01.083
Jay, this isn't funny.

47:01.875 --> 47:02.917
Jay.

47:04.917 --> 47:06.709
Jay! Jay!

47:08.208 --> 47:09.709
(SHARON GASPS)

47:10.875 --> 47:12.500
(SHAKILY) Oh, my God.

47:12.500 --> 47:15.083
(SOBS) Oh, my God. No!

47:15.083 --> 47:17.000
No! No! Jay!

47:17.000 --> 47:18.291
(SOBBING)

47:19.583 --> 47:20.583
Jay!

47:25.417 --> 47:26.792
(SHUDDERS)

47:30.917 --> 47:32.250
(GASPS) No!

47:32.250 --> 47:33.291
No!

47:33.750 --> 47:35.875
No! No!

47:35.875 --> 47:38.125
-(RATTLING)
-(DOORBELL RINGS)

47:39.542 --> 47:40.583
-(MOANING)
-(SCREAMING)

47:40.583 --> 47:42.458
-No! No!
-It's okay. It's okay.
It's okay.

47:47.750 --> 47:49.125
-Run!
-No!

47:50.750 --> 47:52.250
(GRUNTING)

47:56.959 --> 47:58.083
(GASPS)

48:00.542 --> 48:02.125
ABIGAIL: Sharon, get inside!

48:02.792 --> 48:04.125
(SHARON GRUNTS)

48:06.166 --> 48:07.917
(PANTING)

48:07.917 --> 48:09.291
(GRUNTING)

48:14.792 --> 48:16.250
No!

48:16.250 --> 48:17.667
(GRUNTING)

48:19.792 --> 48:21.375
(GASPS)

48:21.375 --> 48:23.000
(SPRINKLER CLICKING)

48:26.500 --> 48:27.542
No.

48:27.542 --> 48:29.959
(SOBBING) No, please! Don't!

48:30.709 --> 48:31.792
(SCREAMS)

48:33.625 --> 48:34.667
(GRUNTS) No!

48:36.792 --> 48:38.291
(PANTING)

48:42.000 --> 48:43.375
(GRUNTING)

48:50.166 --> 48:51.500
(SHARON PANTING)

48:52.333 --> 48:54.166
(MUSIC BOX PLAYING)

49:12.166 --> 49:13.458
(PANTING)

49:22.375 --> 49:23.750
(GASPS) No!

49:25.375 --> 49:26.542
(PANTING)

49:26.542 --> 49:27.709
No!

49:27.709 --> 49:29.250
(SOBING)

49:29.250 --> 49:30.917
(ABIGAIL GRUNTING)

49:35.208 --> 49:36.542
(PANTING)

49:37.041 --> 49:38.333
Sharon!

49:41.208 --> 49:42.875
Sharon! No!

49:44.375 --> 49:45.709
(PANTING)

50:03.875 --> 50:05.583
(DOOR CREAKING)

50:09.542 --> 50:11.375
(SOBBING) Why? Why?

50:16.375 --> 50:17.917
No, please.

50:17.917 --> 50:18.959
Why?

50:19.667 --> 50:21.250
Don't do this to us!

50:21.834 --> 50:22.959
(SCREAMS)

50:25.166 --> 50:26.542
Oh, my God.

50:26.542 --> 50:28.458
-(SHAKILY) Sharon!
-Wojciech!

50:29.750 --> 50:31.333
Wojciech! Shit.

50:31.333 --> 50:32.959
-(SOBBING)
-(MUMBLES)

50:33.917 --> 50:36.583
Where's Abby? Where is she?

50:37.417 --> 50:38.875
I don't know.

50:38.875 --> 50:40.917
I don't know, Wojciech.

50:40.917 --> 50:42.542
(RATTLING)

50:45.458 --> 50:47.750
(SOFTLY) Please, talk to me.
I don't know.

50:47.750 --> 50:49.166
(SOBBING) I don't...

50:50.959 --> 50:52.625
-Please, don't.
-(SHUSHING)

50:53.250 --> 50:55.000
Please.

50:55.000 --> 50:56.583
They're gonna kill us.

50:58.959 --> 51:00.750
No!

51:00.750 --> 51:03.917
-No! Please.
-(SHUSHING)

51:05.542 --> 51:08.458
Don't... Don't kill my baby!

51:08.458 --> 51:09.458
Please.

51:10.250 --> 51:11.625
(YELLS) No!

51:25.583 --> 51:27.000
(CREAKING)

52:01.500 --> 52:03.041
(DOOR CREAKS)

52:34.125 --> 52:38.875
SHARON: (SOBBING)
Please, don't! My baby!
Please! Please!

52:38.875 --> 52:42.208
Please, don't!
Please, don't do this!

52:42.709 --> 52:44.125
Please!

52:44.125 --> 52:45.208
No!

52:45.875 --> 52:47.709
Please, don't!

52:47.709 --> 52:50.583
No! Please, stop!

52:51.333 --> 52:52.792
No. No.

52:52.792 --> 52:53.959
Please, stop.

52:54.917 --> 52:57.125
No. Please, don't do this.

52:57.583 --> 52:58.709
(SOBBING)

52:58.709 --> 53:01.875
Please, don't do this! Please.

53:01.875 --> 53:03.959
-(CRYING) Please don't...
-(DOOR CLOSES)

53:07.709 --> 53:09.417
SHARON: Please don't hurt...

53:29.083 --> 53:30.417
(PANTING)

53:47.792 --> 53:49.125
(CREAKING)

54:07.000 --> 54:08.667
-(WOJCIECH SCREAMS)
-(GASPS)

54:10.000 --> 54:11.458
(GRUNTING)

54:12.625 --> 54:14.542
(PANTS) Abby!

54:14.542 --> 54:15.709
Go!

54:17.125 --> 54:18.333
Go! Come on!

54:19.000 --> 54:20.500
(PANTING)

54:20.500 --> 54:22.375
Abby! Get help!

54:24.500 --> 54:26.333
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

54:26.333 --> 54:27.500
WOJCIECH: No!

54:27.500 --> 54:28.959
(RATTLING)

54:28.959 --> 54:30.625
(WOJCIECH SCREAMS)

54:30.625 --> 54:32.166
(DOOR CLOSES)

54:37.875 --> 54:39.208
(MATCH LIGHTS)

55:16.208 --> 55:17.500
(GASPS)

55:44.083 --> 55:45.417
(PANTING)

56:06.959 --> 56:08.542
ABIGAIL: William!

56:11.959 --> 56:13.917
(WHITE BIRD  PLAYING
ON HEADPHONES)

56:20.291 --> 56:21.792
Hey!

56:21.792 --> 56:23.333
ABIGAIL:
William! Hey! William!

56:23.917 --> 56:24.959
(SIGHS)

56:29.542 --> 56:31.000
(INAUDIBLE)

56:33.458 --> 56:34.792
Hey, hey.

56:37.792 --> 56:39.500
(MUFFLED SCREAMS)

56:58.166 --> 56:59.333
(SIGHS)

57:01.750 --> 57:03.000
(EXHALES)

57:09.250 --> 57:11.291
(MUSIC CONTINUES
OVER HEADPHONES)

57:18.583 --> 57:20.333
(MUFFLED GRUNTING)

57:25.583 --> 57:28.500
-SHARON: No!
-(SHAKILY) Abby, Abby, Abby!

57:28.500 --> 57:30.333
I'm so glad you're okay.

57:30.333 --> 57:31.375
Oh, my God.

57:33.458 --> 57:34.792
(GROANS)

57:34.792 --> 57:37.166
(SOBBING)

57:37.166 --> 57:39.333
Don't, don't, don't,
don't, don't, don't!

57:39.333 --> 57:40.709
Abby!

57:41.500 --> 57:43.125
They're gonna kill us.

57:43.125 --> 57:45.125
(SOBBING)
They're gonna kill my baby.

57:45.125 --> 57:46.208
No.

57:46.208 --> 57:47.250
(SNIFFLES)

57:47.917 --> 57:49.250
Hope, Sharon.

57:50.208 --> 57:52.000
Don't lose hope.

57:52.000 --> 57:54.500
-(DOOR BREAKS OPEN)
-(SHARON MUMBLES)

57:54.500 --> 57:56.625
Let them go. Take me.
But let the girls go, man.

57:56.625 --> 57:59.250
-(GRUNTS)
-(YELLS) No! No! No!

57:59.250 --> 58:00.709
-(GROANS)
-(SOBBING)

58:00.709 --> 58:03.041
Abby! Abby! No!

58:03.041 --> 58:04.417
(GRUNTING)

58:05.208 --> 58:06.875
Stop, stop, stop, man!

58:08.083 --> 58:09.875
(SOBBING INCONSOLABLY)

58:10.542 --> 58:11.917
(CHOKING)

58:13.458 --> 58:14.750
(GROANING)

58:18.667 --> 58:21.542
Ah! No! Ah!

58:21.542 --> 58:24.125
(SOBBING) No, please, don't!
Please, don't!

58:24.917 --> 58:26.792
(WAILING)

58:28.000 --> 58:29.750
Don't! Don't!

58:29.750 --> 58:32.041
-Abby, no!
-No! Sharon!

58:32.041 --> 58:34.083
ABIGAIL: Stop!
SHARON: Don't kill my baby!

58:34.083 --> 58:35.792
Please, no!

58:37.208 --> 58:39.583
-Abby!
-No, Sharon!

58:39.583 --> 58:40.750
-Sharon!
-No!

58:42.041 --> 58:43.417
(SOBBING)

58:56.417 --> 58:58.083
Hey, Abby.

59:03.375 --> 59:05.917
You don't give up, okay?

59:05.917 --> 59:07.709
Not right now.
You have to try.

59:07.709 --> 59:09.166
You promised me
that you would.

59:11.250 --> 59:12.834
We don't deserve this.

59:14.583 --> 59:16.417
No one deserves this.

59:16.417 --> 59:18.458
No, I know. I know.

59:25.792 --> 59:27.125
Oh, fuck.

59:29.083 --> 59:30.417
We gotta do something.

59:30.417 --> 59:31.667
I can't.

59:32.333 --> 59:33.625
Come on, Abby.

59:42.041 --> 59:43.834
Let's go back to that beach.

59:45.000 --> 59:48.333
You and me.
Let's go back to Zuma.

59:48.333 --> 59:51.000
I wanna keep
having that conversation
we were having.

59:51.000 --> 59:53.125
You told me that you
couldn't remember
what we talked about.

59:53.125 --> 59:55.959
But I remember.
I remember with all my heart.

59:55.959 --> 01:00:00.291
About living in France,
how you loved
working with those kids.

01:00:00.959 --> 01:00:02.792
And Marlowe.

01:00:02.792 --> 01:00:06.041
We bonded
over Christopher Marlowe.

01:00:06.041 --> 01:00:07.959
I didn't know
what you were talking about.

01:00:07.959 --> 01:00:09.792
-(CRYING)
-But it didn't matter.

01:00:10.417 --> 01:00:12.500
(SNIFFLES) I knew it.

01:00:15.542 --> 01:00:17.542
What do you say?

01:00:17.542 --> 01:00:19.500
You and me. Let's go to Zuma.

01:00:28.458 --> 01:00:29.917
What are you gonna do?

01:00:30.917 --> 01:00:32.166
Not give up.

01:00:41.041 --> 01:00:42.375
(SCREAMS)

01:00:46.375 --> 01:00:47.417
(GRUNTS)

01:00:47.875 --> 01:00:49.000
No!

01:00:49.834 --> 01:00:51.083
(GRUNTING)

01:00:54.875 --> 01:00:56.875
WOJCIECH: Go! Run! Go, go! Go!

01:00:59.875 --> 01:01:01.667
Wojciech, come on!

01:01:02.041 --> 01:01:03.500
WOJCIECH: Abby.

01:01:08.542 --> 01:01:09.834
(GRUNTS)

01:01:11.583 --> 01:01:12.625
(GASPS)

01:01:13.333 --> 01:01:15.083
(SCREAMS) No!

01:01:15.083 --> 01:01:16.750
-No!
-(SCREAMING)

01:01:20.000 --> 01:01:21.291
Go! Go!

